# http://duti.org/documentation.html
# This is a duti config file to set default applications for file types or extensions (UTIs)

# Blank lines and lines beginning with a '#' are ignored
# If the file doesn't end with a blank line, duti might give a "line too long" error.

# To know the bundle id of a specific app:
# osascript -e "id of app \"<app_name>\""

# List of Uniform Type Identifiers in mac OS:
# /System/Library/Frameworks/CoreServices.framework/Frameworks/LaunchServices.framework/Versions/A/Support/lsregister -dump > UTIs

# Format:
# [Bundle ID] [ UTI | ext | MIME type ] [role]

# Valid roles:
#
# all     app handles all roles for the given UTI.
# viewer  app handles reading and displaying documents with given UTI.
# editor  app can manipulate and save the item. Implies viewer.
# shell   app can execute the item.
# none    app cannot open the item, but provides an icon for the given UTI.

com.github.atom markdown all
com.github.atom public.plain-text all
com.github.atom public.source-code  all

org.videolan.vlc .avi all
org.videolan.vlc .mkv all
org.videolan.vlc .mp4 all
